<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A newly released book with nude photos of
a woman purported to be Premier Andreas Papandreou's girlfriend is
selling rapidly throughout the capital.
   The book's title, ``Liani Supports Change,'' is a pun referring
to Dimitra Liani, 35, and the ruling Panhellenic Socialist
Movement's slogan, ``People Support Change.''
   ``Sales have been fantastic and I'm sure I'll sell out today,''
said one newsstand owner.
   Two conservative newspapers and one left-wing journal, which
reprinted photos of the nude woman on its front page, said an
examination of the photographs determined they were authentic.
   Author George Karatzaferis said he would not disclose the origin
of the photographs.
   ``We've had the pictures for a while but decided to publish them
when Mr. Papandreou made clear he wants to identify Greece with
Liani,'' he said.
   Liani, a former Olympic Airways flight attendant, escorted
Papandreou, 70, during an official visit by Nicaraguan President
Daniel Ortega this week and at a meeting with Bulgarian leader
Todor Zhivkov last month.
   Papandreou filed for divorce in March from his American-born
wife, Margaret.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Marlo Thomas injured her neck in an
automobile accident in Connecticut, her spokeswoman said.
   The accident occurred Wednesday when the car she was riding in
was struck from behind, spokeswoman Marybeth Edmonds said Friday.
   The actress suffered whiplash and was treated by a private
physician, she said, but continued to have ``very bad pains'' and
was resting at home.
   The car had to be towed away, but no one else was seriously
injured, she said.
   Ms. Thomas, best known for her television show ``That Girl,'' is
married to talk show host Phil Donahue. They have a home in
Westport, Conn.
