<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Academy award-winning actress Patty Duke wants
Congress to put more money into mental health research.
   Duke delivered petitions Friday containing 400,000 signatures of
relatives of victims of mental illness to the Senate Appropriations
subcommittee on Labor, Health and Human Services.
   ``There is treatment. You do get well,'' said the actress, whose
own battle against manic-depression was chronicled in the
autobiography ``Call Me Anna.''
   ``Having been through it, you don't want others to go through
it,'' she added, speaking on behalf of the National Alliance for
the Mentally Ill.
   Duke was the youngest actress to win an Academy Award when she
was named best actress in 1963 for her portrayal of the blind, deaf
and mute Helen Keller in the film version of ``The Miracle Worker.''
