<FIRST>r a PM-PromDates     05-06 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Prom Dates,0196</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shut Out of Iowa Dance, Prom Couple Gets Invitations Elsewhere</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBURNETT, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Denied permission to attend the hometown
prom, a high school student and his married date are getting
invitations to dance at proms across the country.
   Jayme Wessels, 17, wanted to take family friend Delores
Washburn, 35, to the Alburnett prom last weekend but the school
board denied permission, saying it was inappropriate for a student
to bring a date who was married.
   A judge upheld the school's decision, and they stayed home. But
word of their case spread around the country and invitations to
attend other proms are streaming in.
   ``I think they've had a dozen invitations from high school proms
across the country,'' said Mrs. Washburn's husband, Don.
   Wessels said a Jacksonville, Fla., radio station is trying to
line up a prom for them, and one Chicago station has arranged for
the couple to attend a prom May 12. Both have agreed to pay for the
couple's airplane trip.
   ``I'm real excited about it,'' said Wessels. He said, however, a
school landscaping project may force him to sit out the May 12 prom.
</TEXT>
