<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--China-Crash     05-06 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--China-Crash,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Helicopter Crashes While Returning From Oil Rig; 10 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A helicopter carrying Chinese workers from an
offshore oil rig crashed near a port in northeastern China, killing
all 10 people on board, the official Xinhua News Agency said
Saturday.
   The two pilots and eight off-duty workers were being shuttled
from the Bohai Petroleum Corp. platform to the city of Tianjin when
the U.S.-made Bell-412 helicopter crashed at the city's port, the
agency said.
   One of the pilots was Japanese and the rest on board were
Chinese, the agency said.
   The helicopter was owned by Aero Asahi Corp. of Japan and leased
to the Tianjin branch of the China Offshore Helicopter Service
Corporation. The cause of the crash was not known.
</TEXT>
