<SECOND>AM-BRF--Jet Fire,0129</SECOND>
<HEAD>Minor Fire Reported Aboard Lufthansa Jet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small fire broke out in the cargo hold of a
Lufthansa Boeing 747 with 263 passengers aboard shortly after it
took off, forcing the plane back to Hong Kong, an airline spokesman
said Saturday.
   No one was injured in the incident, said Claus Dehio, public
relations manager for the German airline.
   The jetliner landed Friday, 18 minutes after leaving the British
colony for Bangkok, because smoke warning signals were activated in
the rear cargo compartment, Dehio said.
   The fire extinguishing system aboard the jetliner put out the
fire before the plane landed in Hong Kong, he said. Dehio said the
blaze was believed caused by overheating in the cargo area.
