<HEAD>Dozens of Tourists Injured in Truck-Bus Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sightseeing bus filled with West German tourists
smashed into a parked truck Saturday, injuring 38 people, officials
said.
   Several of the tourists were in serious condition at three Rome
hospitals, but others had lesser injuries and were treated and
released, said a spokesman for the West German Embassy.
   The bus driver apparently did not immediately see the truck,
which was stopped in the emergency lane of the Rome-Florence
highway, a fire department official said. The driver hit the brakes
but slammed into the back of the truck, stopped just north of Rome,
he said.
   The right side of the bus was sheared off by the impact, the
Italian news agency ANSA reported.
   The injured were all on the sightseeing bus.
