<SECOND>AM-Peru-Bus Plunge,0142</SECOND>
<HEAD>21 Die When Bus Rolls Off Cliff</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A passenger bus maneuvering tight curves on a
mountain road rolled off a cliff, killing 21 passengers and
injuring 21, police said Saturday.
   The privately owned bus bounced down a 400-foot canyon Thursday
near Cachicadan, a town high in the Andes Mountains 275 miles north
of Lima, police said.
   Survivors said the driver stopped on the road before attempting
a turn, and the bus rolled backward off the cliff, police said.
   Police said a mechanical fault is the suspected cause of the
crash, but they did not elaborate. Word of the disaster was delayed
in reaching Lima because the site is isolated.
   The injured were hospitalized in nearby towns.
   Police said the bus was en route to Cachicadan from Trujillo, 95
miles west.
