<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--CockfightRaid     05-06 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Cockfight Raid,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>180 Arrested in Cockfight Raid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DANIELSVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities raided a cockfighting arena
complete with bleachers and concession stands Saturday and arrested
about 180 people from four states.
   John Bankhead, a spokesman for the Georgia Bureau of
Investigation, said authorities raided the 300-square-foot tin-roof
shed around noon. He said more than 200 people were attending
fights in three rings.
   Ten people, including the organizers of the event and the
property owner, were charged with commercial gambling and cruelty
to animals. About 170 others, mostly spectators, were charged only
with cruelty to animals.
   Authorities also confiscated about $30,000 in cash, guns,
marijuana and cocaine, Bankhead said.
   The fights, Bankhead said, were regularly scheduled events in
this northeast Georgia community. ``It's been going on awhile. We
just found out about it three months ago, and started sending
undercover people in,'' he said.
