<HEAD>$adv06</HEAD>
<HEAD>$adv07</HEAD>
<HEAD>For release weekend editions May 6-7</HEAD>
<HEAD>UNDATED: pork products.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Grain and soybean futures advanced on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Wheat for May delivery settled Friday at $4.37 a bushel, up from
$4.17{ a week earlier; May corn rose to $2.80{ a bushel from
$2.69\; May oats jumped to $1.96} a bushel from $1.78{; May
soybeans climbed to $7.59{ a bushel from $7.22{.
   Livestock and meat futures were mostly higher on the Chicago
Mercantile Exchange.
   June live cattle rose to 72.42 cents a pound from 71.45 cents;
May feeder cattle rallied to 76.97 cents a pound from 76.52 cents;
June live hogs climbed to 47.27 a pound from 46.62 cents; May
frozen pork bellies dropped to 30.95 cents a pound from 31.37 cents.
   Gold and silver prices fell moderately on New York's Commodity
Exchange.
   June gold dropped to $379.30 a troy ounce from $380.50; May
silver slid to $5.598 a troy ounce from $5.601.
   Gasoline, crude oil and heating oil prices retreated on New
York's Mercantile Exchange.
   West Texas Intermediate crude oil for June delivery fell to
$20.02 a barrel from $20.43; June heating oil slipped to 40.85
cents a gallon from 49.77 cents; unleaded gasoline dropped to 67.50
cents from 71.22 cents.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End adv for weekend editions May 6-7</NOTE>
